d 'CSESTUDY': module to provide Efficient Inference for Cross-Sectional Event Studies
d
d  csestudy implements the time-series approach to cross-sectional
d event study inference described in Cohn, Johnson, Liu, and
d Wardlaw (2026), "Past is Prologue: Inference from the Cross
d Section of Returns Around an Event," Journal of Financial
d Economics 180, 104278. Standard event study methodologies
d typically fail to account for the cross-correlation structure in
d stock returns across firm characteristics, and clustering
d standard errors by industry does not address this. The command
d benchmarks the event-period coefficient against a distribution of
d the same relationship estimated on pre-event days, using either
d OLS or GLS with a PCA-based covariance estimator. Rejection
d criteria are reported as a parametric z-score and a p-value from
d the empirical CDF of pre-event coefficients. 
d
d KW: event study
d KW: cross sectional data
d KW: corporate finance
d
d Requires: Stata version 14
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260420
d
